\id XXF - Aboriginal Plain English Version
\toc1 A Little Book about the Bible About this book
\mt1 A Little Book about the Bible
\b
\pc A book to help people
\pc learn from the Holy Bible,
\pc using the Plain English Version
\b
\b
\b
\c 1
\mt1 About this book
\ip I wrote this \it Little Book about the Bible \it*to help people know more about the Holy Bible.
\b
\ip I used plain English in this little book, the same as we used in the Holy Bible, Plain English Version (PEV). Anybody can use this little book, but I wrote it mostly for Indigenous Australians that grew up talking their own language, and then later they learned to talk English. I wrote this little book to help people understand the Bible better.
\b
\ip We can learn a lot of things from the Holy Bible. This little book just talks about some of those things. It tells you what the Bible says about those things. The words that are in
\q1 this sort of print
\ip are from the Holy Bible, PEV.
\b
\ip This little book also tells you where to look in the Bible to find out more. So you can use this little book for Bible studies.
\b
\ip I want to thank all the people that helped me write this little book. Some of them were Aboriginal Australians and some were white-fellas.
\b
\ipr Dave Glasgow
