\ms1 Part 1 // Why is the Holy Bible important?
\p Everyone should read or listen to the Bible because it is a very important book.
\b
\p \bd It is God’s word\bd*. That means that it has \bd God’s message to us people\bd*. It tells us the things that God wants us to know about himself, and about spirits, and things that last for ever. If we read it or listen to it, and if we take notice of it, God can take us into his family.
\s1 If we have a Bible with us, will it help us?
\p What if we get a Bible and leave it on the shelf all the time, and we never read it. Is that all right? Will it help us? Or if we put it under the pillow of a sick person, will it help that person get better?
\b
\p Well, it is good to remember that God’s word is powerful, but \bd we have to read the Bible\bd*. Then it can help us. Or we can listen to somebody else read it. The message in the Bible is powerful, but that message has to get into our heads before we can know that power. If you believe the Bible’s message, and if you do what it says, God will take you into his family. That is the good way the Bible helps us.
\b
\p This is what the Bible says in the book that has the name \it The letter that James wrote\it*, in chapter 1 at verse 18,
\q1 God wanted us to be in his own family, so he sent his true word to us. And when we believed that word it was like we were born all over again. That’s how he made us his really special people.
\b
\p What if we get a Bible and read it, or listen to somebody else read it, but then we just forget it and take no notice of it, is that all right? No. That is not all right. It is very important that we \bd take notice of the message in the Bible\bd*, so that it can change us and make us better people.
\b
\p This is what the Bible says in the book called \it The letter that James wrote\it*, in chapter 1 at verses 21 and 25,
\q1 You have to listen properly to the word from God, that he put right inside you, and you have to do what it says. Don’t think that you are so good that you don’t need God’s word. No. You have to do what it says, then that word will save you. … You have to listen to God’s word and keep on thinking about it. Don’t forget it, but do everything it says. That word will make you free, so that you will do everything God wants. And God will make you really happy whenever you do the things he wants you to do.
\b
\p So you see, everybody needs to do the things in the Bible that God tells us to do.
\s1 Where is God’s power in the Bible?
\p Is God’s power in the book with a cover, that has pages made out of paper and ink? Do they have God’s power? No. \bd God’s power is in the message\bd* in the Bible. If we take notice of that message, and believe it, and if we do what it tells us to do, God will take us into his family and use his power to change us into his good people, to live with him for ever. It is good to read or listen to a part of the Bible for a little while every day, and think about it. Ask God to teach you what he wants you to learn from it. He will do that, and you will learn more and become strong for him.
\b
\p We wrote this little book to help you use the Holy Bible, and to understand its message better. You can learn more about God’s word if you think about these verses.
\b
\ili1 * In \it The 2nd letter that Paul wrote to Timothy\it*, at chapter 3, in verses 16 and 17 it says,
\q1 Everything in God’s book comes from God himself. It was God that sent the message to people to write down, and God uses it now to teach us his true word, and he uses it to get us to understand the things that are wrong with our lives, and he uses it to fix us up, and he uses it to teach us to do the things that are right. That’s how God properly trains his workers. He uses the words in his book to teach them, so they can do all those good things that he wants them to do.
\b
\ili1 * And this is in the book that has the name \it Some important parts of the good news about Jesus that Matthew wrote\it*, at chapter 4, in verses 3 and 4,
\q1 At that time the devil came to Jesus and said, “If you are the son of God, tell these stones to turn into loaves of bread.” But Jesus told him, “No. I will not do that. You know what God says. These words are in his book, ‘People don’t live just by eating bread, but they live by every word that God says.’”
\b
\p You can also think about what the Bible says in \it John wrote this good news about Jesus\it*, in chapter 15, at verse 3, and in \it Mark wrote this good news about Jesus\it*, at chapter 4, in verses 2 to 9, and in verses 14 to 20, and in \it The 2nd letter that Paul wrote to Timothy\it*, in chapter 2, at verse 9.
\s1 We have to understand the message of the Holy Bible.
\p Whenever we read or listen to a version of the Bible, we have to understand the words and language, so that we can understand the message. Do you talk an Aboriginal language? Or do you talk a language from the Torres Strait? If you have a translation in your own language, or another language you can understand, that is the best Bible for you.
\b
\p But maybe you haven’t got a Bible in your own language. Well, you can try reading the Holy Bible, Plain English Version (PEV). It uses easy English words, and it says things in the way that Aboriginal languages say things, so it is easy to understand.
\b
\p We haven’t translated all of the Holy Bible into plain English yet, but you can get most of the New Testament and some of the Old Testament in PEV.
\b
\p In this little book we are copying the PEV words every time we want to tell you the words that the Bible has. And sometimes we explain something about the PEV. We hope this little book will help you understand the Bible better, and help you live by it.
\s1 How to get the PEV.
\s2 Printed books
\p You can get Plain English Version (PEV) books with parts of the Holy Bible from the Bible League. You can call them on 1800 800 937 or go to the \it store\it* on their website \it bl.org.au\it*
\s2 On your phone
\p If you have an android smartphone you can download the PEV app. Click on the “Play Store” app, then search for “Plain English Version Bible”, click on it, and click on “Install”. You can read and listen to the PEV on that app.
\b
\p The PEV is also available in the Australian Bibles app on both iPhones and androids. That app has the Holy Bible in lots of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander languages. You can pick “English” to read or listen to the PEV.
\b
\p And the PEV is in the YouVersion Bible app on both iPhones and androids too.
\b
\p You can use the QR codes on the next page to get some of those apps.
\s2 On your computer
\p You can read and listen to the PEV on a computer too. Go to the Aboriginal Bibles website \it aboriginalbibles.org.au/english-plain\it*
\s1 These are some QR codes that let you get the PEV on to your smartphone or computer.
\b
\p Plain English Version Bible app on the Google Play Store
